00:08:19.960 --> 00:08:23.020
All of them except the parts
of Pericles and that was seen

00:08:23.020 --> 00:08:25.440
to be opraful and finally

00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:30.540
in the seventeenth century the
full folio was published in 1694

00:08:30.540 --> 00:08:33.420
and was essentially a
reprint of the third,

00:08:33.420 --> 00:08:37.560
although it's a significant volume,
because it served as a source text

00:08:37.560 --> 00:08:41.530
to many of the eighteenth
century editions of Shakespeare.

00:08:41.530 --> 00:08:44.730
So, the publication of
the restoration folios,

00:08:44.730 --> 00:08:48.320
coincides with the revival
